French film legend Alain Delon dies at 88

File photo taken in April 1963 shows French actor Alain Delon giving in an interview in Tokyo. Delon, who starred in classics such as "Purple Noon" and "The Leopard," has died at age 88, his family said on Aug. 18, 2024.

Talk show durante a Rio Innovation Week

Director Renato Ribeiro is participating in a Talk Show at the fourth edition of Rio Innovation Week, where one of the themes being explored is ''humanization in times of artificial intelligence,'' in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, on August 16, 2024. The global technology and innovation conference is ending this Friday (16). (Photo by Onofre Veras/Thenews2/NurPhoto)

Polish Armed Forces Day Celebrated In Krakow

KRAKOW, POLAND - AUGUST 15, 2024: Colonel Ireneusz Olender, Head of the Central Military Recruitment Center (CWCR) branch in Krakow, seen during the Polish Armed Forces Day celebrations, on August 15, 2024, in Krakow, Lesser Poland Voivodeship, Poland. Polish Armed Forces Day, celebrated on August 15th, honors the Republic of Poland's military. It commemorates the 1920 victory in the Battle of Warsaw during the Polish-Soviet War and was officially established on July 30, 1992. (Photo by Artur Widak/NurPhoto)
